        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "which do not include adjustments.",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            481,
            440,
            499
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Based on the global integration method, here is the consolidated balance sheet",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            544,
            867,
            578
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/68102fc6f98b20ba8649d47303468e7c6618efc09756545628c7a274dad4c6e9.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"2\">P + A (Year 1)</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Capital 200</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Reserves 100</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Result 30</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Conso. Reserves (A) 56</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Minor. Interests (A) 34</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets</td><td>820</td></tr><tr><td>Other liabilities</td><td>400</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            223,
            582,
            748,
            686
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "in which",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            705,
            191,
            721
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "- Consolidated reserves  \\(= 56 = 80\\%\\) \\(\\left[100 + 50 + 20\\right] - 80\\)",
            "Minority interests  \\(= 34 = 20\\%\\)  [100 + 50 + 20]"
        ],
        "bbox": [
            143,
            734,
            761,
            787
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "other assets and other liabilities being just the addition of the corresponding A and P accounts.",
        "bbox": [
            105,
            802,
            869,
            834
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "DIRECT CONSOLIDATION",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            65,
            362,
            81
        ],
        "page_idx": 0
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Consolidation of Year 2",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            108,
            118,
            366,
            134
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "This time we consolidate adjusted accounts for P as follows",
        "bbox": [
            105,
            150,
            688,
            168
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/ea60b97ddfa48b734b4a45dfdb7fc6b5a67a7e3bd733ca87392f2764e1a88735.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"4\">P (Year 2)</td></tr><tr><td rowspan=\"5\">Fin. Invest./A</td><td rowspan=\"5\">80</td><td>Capital</td><td>200</td></tr><tr><td>Reserves</td><td>115</td></tr><tr><td>(a)</td><td>8</td></tr><tr><td>Result</td><td>45</td></tr><tr><td>(a)</td><td>(8)</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets</td><td>530</td><td>Other liabilities</td><td>250</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            110,
            181,
            489,
            284
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/4d9e1a84ddbc72accf85aa4c7ef7bf49dad2abb4dfe4c9dacb1a680c9ced9de3.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"2\">A (Year 2)</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Capital 100\nReserves 60\nResult 30</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets 540</td><td>Other liabilities 350</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            493,
            181,
            875,
            285
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "which give, after global integration again, the following consolidated balance sheet",
        "bbox": [
            108,
            301,
            877,
            333
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/6d2e16f8166f49f08a59daeced7f34d46fa5db7545f7e1d6cfb4eeb42eb5fa0c.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"3\">P + A (Year 2)</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Capital</td><td>200</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Reserves</td><td>123</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Result</td><td>37</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Conso. Reserves (A)</td><td>72</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Minor. Interests (A)</td><td>38</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets</td><td>1,070</td><td>600</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            226,
            341,
            756,
            443
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "where",
        "bbox": [
            110,
            462,
            177,
            477
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "Reserves of  \\(P = 123 = 115 + 8\\)",
            "Result of  \\(\\mathsf{P} = 37 = 45 + (8)\\)",
            "- Consolidated reserves = 72 = 80% * [100 + 60 + 30] - 80",
            "Minority interests  \\(= 38 = 20\\% * [100 + 650 + 30]\\)"
        ],
        "bbox": [
            146,
            493,
            769,
            606
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Justification of consolidated reserves evolution",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            110,
            638,
            629,
            655
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "One difficult issue while processing a consolation is to validate that equity, and in particular group reserves, can be justified just like in a normal accounting approach: opening reserves  \\(+\\)  profit - dividends = closing reserves.",
        "bbox": [
            108,
            670,
            877,
            736
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "That's what we are going to check by using the following appropriate report.",
        "bbox": [
            110,
            749,
            855,
            768
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/4242db792e277a085ebb333c03d7f8af937ac41e967821fc4a9a6a9a15596711.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td></td><td>Year 1 Reserves</td><td>Year 2 Result</td><td>Divid. (-) paid</td><td>Divid. (+)</td><td>P Approp.</td><td>Year 2 Reserves</td></tr><tr><td>Company P</td><td>130</td><td>37</td><td></td><td>8</td><td>(15)</td><td>160</td></tr><tr><td>Company A</td><td>56</td><td>24</td><td>(8)</td><td></td><td></td><td>72</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>186</td><td>61</td><td>(8)</td><td>8</td><td>(15)</td><td>232</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            131,
            778,
            836,
            856
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "PART 2 BASICS OF CONSOLIDATION TECHNIQUES",
        "bbox": [
            302,
            70,
            855,
            87
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The number of lines of this report is the number of companies in the consolidation scope.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            119,
            873,
            154
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (1) contains the contribution of each company in the Year 1 consolidated reserves.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            168,
            873,
            201
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (2) shows the same for the individual result of each company, taking into account that the profit shown is the group profit  \\((24 = 80\\% * 30)\\) .",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            216,
            873,
            250
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (3) shows the group part of dividends paid by each company (A pays a group dividend of 8)",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            264,
            871,
            298
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (4) shows the part of dividends received from group companies (P receive a group dividends of 8)",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            312,
            871,
            346
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (5) shows the dividends paid by the parent company to its shareholders. Obviously there can be an amount only on the P line of this report.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            359,
            873,
            409
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (6) is similar to Column (1), but for Year 2",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            423,
            607,
            442
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "At this stage, we make the following checks:",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            457,
            546,
            473
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "- The total of dividends paid must be equal to the total of dividends received. We recommend to use two columns because one can easily see which company is paying a dividend and which companies are receiving dividends. A single column would be more ambiguous.",
            "- The total line must show that opening reserves + result - P dividends = closing reserves",
            "- And if that total line is correct, then we recommend to check that opening reserves + result - dividends paid + dividends received = closing reserves"
        ],
        "bbox": [
            149,
            488,
            871,
            665
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "When these three checks have been validated, there is a good probability that the consolidated equity is correct.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            681,
            871,
            714
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Justification of minority interests evolution",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            109,
            729,
            580,
            745
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The same question arises for the Minority interests evolution which is summarized in another report, different from the previous one, as follows",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            761,
            871,
            793
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "DIRECT CONSOLIDATION",
        "bbox": [
            111,
            65,
            364,
            81
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/58f7679ab7985606c1f1e1d069a98ec015e1f4c6c8ed07c53a3003f5df3d34af.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td></td><td>Year 1Minor. Int.</td><td>Year 2Result</td><td>Divid. (-)paid</td><td>Divid. (+)</td><td>Year 2Minor. Int.</td></tr><tr><td>Company A</td><td>34</td><td>6</td><td>(2)</td><td></td><td>38</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            149,
            124,
            834,
            178
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The principles are quite similar.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            207,
            415,
            225
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "On each line appear companies for which there are minority interests.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            239,
            785,
            258
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (1) contains the contribution of each company in the Year 1 Minority interests.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            271,
            873,
            305
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (2) shows the minority result of each company  \\((6 = 20\\% * 30)\\)",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            318,
            806,
            339
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (3) shows the dividends paid by A to the  \\(3^{rd}\\)  Parties  \\((20\\% \\star 10)\\)",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            350,
            808,
            371
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (4) is not used for our example, but it could be used for more complex groups structures where companies own other companies, each with minority interests and each company is supposed to pay dividends.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            385,
            873,
            434
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "For each individual line, the sum of all amounts of columns (1) to (4) must be equal to the Year 2 Minority interests.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            448,
            873,
            482
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "We will come back later with a deeper approach about this methodology in a specific chapter.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            497,
            873,
            530
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "8.8 Elimination of dividends paid by a foreign company",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            111,
            562,
            836,
            612
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The situation",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            111,
            628,
            260,
            647
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The situation is similar to the previous one, except for company A whose accounts are in a certain foreign currency CUR. That company is owned by the parent company P with a financial percentage of  \\(80\\%\\)  over Year 1 and Year 2.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            660,
            873,
            711
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "At the end of Year 1, company A pays a gross dividend of 100 EUR to the shareholders while P pays a gross dividend of 150 EUR.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            725,
            873,
            758
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Why is this situation different from the previous one with a classical dividend?",
        "text_level": 3,
        "bbox": [
            109,
            773,
            873,
            808
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The amount of 100 CUR was part of the economical profit of A in Year 1 consolidation and its value was 100 CUR at average rate of that period. After the annual general meeting of company A parent company P receives 80 CUR",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            821,
            871,
            871
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "PART 2 BASICS OF CONSOLIDATION TECHNIQUES",
        "bbox": [
            306,
            71,
            852,
            87
        ],
        "page_idx": 3
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "(80% * 100 CUR) and booked at a value depending of the rate that day. We will suppose P receives from the bank an amount of 110 EUR.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            120,
            871,
            153
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "There is clearly again a double impact in group profit : once in company A accounts for 80 CUR and once in parent company accounts for 110 EUR.",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            168,
            871,
            202
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "With this situation, we have a nice opportunity to consolidate a foreign company with the global integration method. Let's go through the process again and give all explanations at the right moment.",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            216,
            871,
            266
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "We are going to setup first the Year 1 consolidated accounts after currency conversion of company A accounts.",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            281,
            871,
            313
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Then we will book the correct adjustment for the elimination of the dividend.",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            329,
            852,
            346
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "We will produce the Year 2 consolidated figures and check the equity and the minority interests in the same way we did in the previous section.",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            361,
            871,
            393
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Currency conversion of company A accounts - Year 1",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            107,
            409,
            685,
            426
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Let's proceed the way it has been explained in chapter 6 on the basis of the following currency rates",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            440,
            871,
            474
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/135cac0456d0ffe2a2841583e4694ac20de28081a996e01387243f723ddb732f.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td></td><td>Year 1</td><td>Year 2</td></tr><tr><td>Closing rate</td><td>1.5</td><td>1.6</td></tr><tr><td>Average rate</td><td>1.3</td><td>1.4</td></tr><tr><td>Historical rate for Capital</td><td>1.2</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Historical rate for Reserves</td><td>1.1</td><td></td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            244,
            486,
            732,
            571
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/462a2d9fd412a3d543f1a66e504c7292b1d8f8ff8bebff21b06972911a084eec.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"2\">A (Year 1) in CUR</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Capital     1,000</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Reserves    500</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Result      200</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets   4,000</td><td>Other liabilities   2,300</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            111,
            592,
            476,
