        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/21d4cc9a86d726a261a076ef6b7c71fbfdc17d0108bd8ba0f0d25d3c64493fe2.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"3\">A (Year 1) in EUR</td></tr><tr><td rowspan=\"10\"></td><td>Capital</td><td>1,500</td></tr><tr><td>(1)</td><td>(300)</td></tr><tr><td>Reserves</td><td>750</td></tr><tr><td>(2)</td><td>(200)</td></tr><tr><td>Result</td><td>300</td></tr><tr><td>(3)</td><td>(40)</td></tr><tr><td>Trans. Adj.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>(1)</td><td>300</td></tr><tr><td>(2)</td><td>200</td></tr><tr><td>(3)</td><td>40</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets</td><td>6,000</td><td>Other liabilities</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            489,
            592,
            856,
            743
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "We translate all accounts of the balance sheet with the closing rate 1.5 and then adjust equity accounts with historical rate and average rate as follows.",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            751,
            871,
            784
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Adjustment (1) reclassifies 300 to translation adjustment because historical rate for this account is 1.2 instead of 1.5.",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            799,
            869,
            831
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Adjustment (2) reclassifies 200 to translation adjustment because historical rate for this account is 1.1 instead of 1.5.",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            847,
            869,
            879
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "DIRECT CONSOLIDATION",
        "bbox": [
            111,
            65,
            364,
            81
        ],
        "page_idx": 4
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Adjustment (3) reclassifies 40 to translation adjustment because profit must be translated at average rate 1.3 instead of closing rate 1.5.",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            119,
            877,
            154
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Currency conversion of company A accounts = Year 2",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            109,
            168,
            689,
            184
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/d175d8217c8276b4847c116847663d964072a4e0d076d5c6f636d38d12ed26a3.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"2\">A (Year 2)</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Capital 1,000</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Reserves 600</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Result 300</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets 5,400</td><td>Other liabilities 3,500</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            111,
            200,
            478,
            293
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/9cfced5d713115bb4db2a9a73c15faec9b6ee0003884be8894b44717d39f4440.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"2\">A (Year 2) in EUR</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Capital \n(4) 1,600 \n(400)</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Reserves \n(5) 960 \n(280)</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Result \n(6) 480 \n(60)</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Trans. Adj. \n(4) 400 \n(5) 280 \n(6) 60</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets</td><td>8,640</td></tr><tr><td>Other liabilities</td><td>5,600</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            493,
            200,
            860,
            353
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "After translation of the whole balance sheet at closing rate 1.6, we adjust equity accounts as follows",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            371,
            875,
            404
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Adjustment (4) reclassifies 400 to translation adjustment because historical rate for this account is 1.2 instead of 1.6.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            419,
            875,
            451
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Adjustment (5) reclassifies 280 to translation adjustment because the amount of reserves of 600 CUR consists of 500 CUR at historical of 1.1 and 100 CUR transferred from the Year 1 profit, initially translated at average rate of 1.3, which gives a historical amount of  \\(500 * 1.1 + 100 * 1.3 = 680\\)  instead of 960.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            467,
            875,
            546
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Adjustment (6) reclassifies 60 to translation adjustment because profit must be translated at average rate 1.4 instead of closing rate 1.6.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            546,
            875,
            580
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Consolidation of Year 1",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            109,
            596,
            369,
            612
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here are the parent statutory company accounts and the consolidated accounts",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            628,
            875,
            660
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/2c0c3a95edbd36c74989d5b1fc95c70f8761d50cc79e919750ae0fd6e83ddf42.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"4\">P (Year 1)</td></tr><tr><td>Fin. Invest./A</td><td>800</td><td>Capital</td><td>2,000</td></tr><tr><td></td><td></td><td>Reserves</td><td>1,000</td></tr><tr><td></td><td></td><td>Result</td><td>300</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets</td><td>4,200</td><td>Other liabilities</td><td>1,700</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            265,
            671,
            738,
            771
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "PART 2 BASICS OF CONSOLIDATION TECHNIQUES",
        "bbox": [
            305,
            71,
            854,
            87
        ],
        "page_idx": 5
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/5ba7efc54196c73c1c84e08f762cb4367500d5c0b933942ae6f2fdf83167ec66.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"3\">P + A (Year 1)</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Capital</td><td>2,000</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Reserves</td><td>1,000</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Result</td><td>300</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Conso. Reserves (A)</td><td>808</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Minor. Interests (A)</td><td>510</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Trans. Adj.</td><td>432</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets</td><td>10,200</td><td>Other liabilities</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            188,
            117,
            798,
            248
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "where",
        "bbox": [
            110,
            265,
            173,
            279
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "- Consolidated Reserves (A) = 808 = 80% * [1500 + (300) + 750 + (200) + 300 + (40)] - 800",
            "Minority Interests (A)  \\(= 510 = 20\\%\\)  \\* [1500 + (300) + 750 + (200)  \\(+300 + (40) + 300 + 200 + 40]\\)",
            "Translation Adj.  \\(= 432 = 80\\%\\)  \\* [300 + 200 + 40]"
        ],
        "bbox": [
            146,
            279,
            875,
            395
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "As explained in chapter 6, consolidated reserves never include translation adjustments amount in order to be able to justify the evolution of reserves in an accounting way without mixing up currency effects.",
        "bbox": [
            108,
            408,
            875,
            459
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "We keep a specific account which shows the group part in this amount.",
        "bbox": [
            108,
            472,
            796,
            489
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Consolidation of Year 2",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            108,
            505,
            366,
            522
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "With the same arguments as for the classical dividend seen in previous section, we have to eliminate in the parent company profit the part of that dividend that was included in the Year 1 profit of company A. We are speaking about  \\(80\\%\\)  * 100 CUR * 1.3 = 104 EUR.",
        "bbox": [
            108,
            537,
            875,
            601
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "But P has received an amount of dividend of 110 EUR as mentioned initially. From a consolidation point of view, we consider two amounts: 104 corresponding to the dividend and 6 considered as an exchange gain. Theoretically speaking, P should have received exactly 104. If more it is indeed a gain, if less it is a loss.",
        "bbox": [
            108,
            617,
            872,
            699
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here is the adjustment eliminating that dividend",
        "bbox": [
            108,
            713,
            584,
            730
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/3e7647af7dc95df35d7c6ed556f8fbd24f7ff9459f78af1f167cbdd7fb2191da.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td></td><td>Debit</td><td>Credit</td></tr><tr><td>Financial income (dividends)</td><td>110</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Exchange gain</td><td></td><td>6</td></tr><tr><td>Reserves</td><td></td><td>104</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            262,
            749,
            764,
            818
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "and we can see that we eliminate the 110 from the Financial income but we reclassify 6 on the Exchange gain, corresponding to a correct view for",
        "bbox": [
            108,
            841,
            872,
            875
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "DIRECT CONSOLIDATION",
        "bbox": [
            112,
            65,
            366,
            81
        ],
        "page_idx": 6
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "consolidation. Reserves are impacted only by the dividend amount valuated at average rate of Year 1.",
        "bbox": [
            100,
            117,
            880,
            151
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The reason to proceed that way is, in particular, for audit purpose. It is indeed more easy to check that this specific account has been set to zero.",
        "bbox": [
            100,
            166,
            877,
            201
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Let's now consider parent statutory accounts and the consolidated accounts, including that adjustment.",
        "bbox": [
            100,
            215,
            873,
            248
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/0337eadd2374611dc7ab4c5c9ccdaebf919a1837f776bc5d67914c5f83d067ce.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"4\">P (Year 2)</td></tr><tr><td rowspan=\"5\">Fin. Invest./A</td><td rowspan=\"5\">800</td><td>Capital</td><td>2,000</td></tr><tr><td>Reserves</td><td>1,150</td></tr><tr><td>(a)</td><td>104</td></tr><tr><td>Result</td><td>450</td></tr><tr><td>(a)</td><td>(104)</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets</td><td>5,300</td><td>Other liabilities</td><td>2,500</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            261,
            275,
            738,
            391
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/f81a69740f86ab7db2d85bc77c8d35d5fcc5ecdd2e8a3fd7142a2a438616e864.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td colspan=\"3\">P + A (Year 2)</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Capital</td><td>2,000</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Reserves</td><td>1,254</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Result</td><td>346</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Conso. Reserves (A)</td><td>1,040</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Minor. Interests (A)</td><td>608</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>Trans. Adj.</td><td>592</td></tr><tr><td>Other assets</td><td>13,940</td><td>Other liabilities</td></tr><tr><td></td><td></td><td>8,100</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            203,
            419,
            820,
            553
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "where",
        "text_level": 4,
        "bbox": [
            104,
            571,
            171,
            586
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "list",
        "sub_type": "text",
        "list_items": [
            "- Consolidated Reserves (A) = 1040 = 80% * [1600 + (400) + 960 + (280) + 480 + (60)] - 800",
            "Minority Interests (A) = 608 = 20% * [1600 + (400) + 960 + (280) + 480 + (60) + 400 + 280 + 60]",
            "Translation Adj. = 592 = 80% [400 + 280 + 60]"
        ],
        "bbox": [
            143,
            600,
            877,
            715
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Justification of consolidated reserves evolution",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            104,
            731,
            629,
            749
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Let's check if consolidated reserves evolution can be justified in an accounting way by using the same report as for the classical dividend.",
        "bbox": [
            104,
            764,
            877,
            798
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "PART 2 BASICS OF CONSOLIDATION TECHNIQUES",
        "bbox": [
            299,
            69,
            858,
            85
        ],
        "page_idx": 7
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/1b54f7a9fa67e48d65f4d409d0b9e3a7933dfe9e085d09d19136fed7187464ad.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td></td><td>Year 1 Reserves</td><td>Year 2 Result</td><td>Divid, (-)</td><td>Divid. (+)</td><td>P Approp.</td><td>Year 2 Reserves</td></tr><tr><td>Company P</td><td>1,300</td><td>346</td><td></td><td>104</td><td>(150)</td><td>1,600</td></tr><tr><td>Company A</td><td>808</td><td>336</td><td>(104)</td><td></td><td></td><td>1,040</td></tr><tr><td></td><td>2,108</td><td>682</td><td>(104)</td><td>104</td><td>(150)</td><td>2,640</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            130,
            129,
            873,
            207
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (1) contains the contribution of each company in the Year 1 consolidated reserves",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            238,
            880,
            270
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (2) shows the same for the individual result of each company, taking into account that the profit shown is the group profit  \\(336 = 80\\% * [480 + (60)]\\)",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            287,
            880,
            337
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (3) shows the group part of dividends paid by each company (A pays a group dividend of 104)",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            351,
            880,
            385
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (4) shows the part of dividends received from group companies (P receive a group dividends of 104)",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            400,
            880,
            434
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (5) shows the dividends paid by the parent company to its shareholders",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            447,
            880,
            481
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (6) is similar to Column (1), but for Year 2",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            497,
            610,
            515
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "and reading the total line, we get \"Opening reserves  \\(+\\)  group profit - parent dividend = Closing reserves\".",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            528,
            880,
            562
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Justification of minority interests evolution",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            107,
            578,
            584,
            594
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The same question arises for the Minority Interests evolution which is summarized in the following report",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            609,
            880,
            643
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "table",
        "img_path": "images/631e1ecfc9413e2259f57a8d80f441cfc8f6ef3e9268f284437b77471f871f26.jpg",
        "table_caption": [],
        "table_footnote": [],
        "table_body": "<table><tr><td></td><td>Year 1Minor. Int.</td><td>Year 2Result</td><td>Divid. (-)paid</td><td>Divid, (+)</td><td>Trans.Adj.</td><td>Year 2Minor. Int.</td></tr><tr><td>Company A</td><td>510</td><td>84</td><td>(26)</td><td></td><td>40</td><td>608</td></tr></table>",
        "bbox": [
            126,
            668,
            871,
            718
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (1) contains the contribution of each company in the Year 1 minority interests",
        "bbox": [
            104,
            746,
            877,
            780
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (2) shows the same for the individual minority result of each company  \\((84 = 20\\% * [480 + (60)])\\)",
        "bbox": [
            104,
            795,
            877,
            830
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (3) shows the dividends paid by A to the  \\(3^{rd}\\)  Parties, that is  \\(26 = 20\\%\\)",
        "bbox": [
            107,
            843,
            877,
            876
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "DIRECT CONSOLIDATION",
        "bbox": [
            111,
            64,
            366,
            79
        ],
        "page_idx": 8
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (4) is not used for our example",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            119,
            500,
            135
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Column (5) is the contribution in the translation adjustments variation between Year 1 and Year 2 for  \\(40 = 20\\%\\)  \\*  \\([400 + 280 + 60] - [300 + 200 + 40]\\) .",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            150,
            877,
            201
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "8.9 Elimination of interim dividends",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            109,
            233,
            691,
            255
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The situation",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            109,
            277,
            261,
            293
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Interim dividend is a dividend decided during the current year instead of a classical dividend that is decided at the end of current year and paid after the general meeting, a few months after the closing.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            309,
            875,
            358
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The reason to pay an interim dividend is generally to transfer cash to the shareholder earlier than what would happen with a classical dividend. It is also a way to improve the current year statutory profit of the shareholder.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            374,
            875,
            423
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In consolidation, we are faced to a similar problem of double impact on the consolidated profit, once in the company paying the interim dividend and once in the shareholders' accounts receiving it. And moreover, this double impact occurs during the same year.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            438,
            875,
            502
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "We thus have to eliminate the financial income booked in the shareholders' accounts in a similar way we did it for the two previous situations.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            517,
            873,
            551
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "However, we will not develop again a complete case study but we will focus on how to book that interim dividend in both company A accounts and shareholders' accounts.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            565,
            875,
            615
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "We suppose interim dividends are paid",
        "text_level": 3,
        "bbox": [
            111,
            631,
            537,
            647
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here are the accounts of company A owned by parent company P with a financial percentage of  \\(80\\%\\) . We suppose that an interim dividend of 10 is decided and will be paid in very short term, before the end of the year.",
        "bbox": [
            109,
            662,
            875,
            711
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    },
    {
        "type": "header",
        "text": "PART 2 BASICS OF CONSOLIDATION TECHNIQUES",
        "bbox": [
            305,
            71,
            856,
            87
        ],
        "page_idx": 9
    }
]